---
import ClerriLayout from '../../layouts/ClerriLayout.astro';
---
<ClerriLayout title="Market Context" section="market">

<div class="page-head">
  <div class="page-eyebrow">02 · Market Context</div>
  <h1 class="page-title">The wind is at our back. <em>Loudly.</em></h1>
  <p class="page-sub">Verified data on dental insurance landscape, PPO compression, DSO consolidation, and the demographic gap Clerri's pitch lands inside of.</p>
</div>

<div class="page-body">

  <div class="callout zest-hi">
    <div class="lbl">The Single Most Resonant Hook</div>
    <p style="font-size:1.1rem"><strong>"Nearly 30% of dentists dropped out of insurance networks in Q4 2024."</strong> — ADA Health Policy Institute, Q4 2024 Survey. Lead messaging here across all channels.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>The structural setup</h2>
  <div class="grid-2">
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-rose">Coverage Gap</span>
      <h4>72M+ adults uninsured for dental</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.9rem">27% of US adults have no dental insurance (CareQuest 2024 SOHEA). NADP 2025: total dental benefits enrollment <strong>declined 2.3% year-over-year</strong> — commercial -2.0%, public -3.0%. <strong>Only 29.2% of elderly Americans</strong> have dental benefits.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-rose">PPO Compression</span>
      <h4>30-45% revenue write-offs</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.9rem">PPO plans = 80%+ of dental benefits market but reimburse &lt;50% of provider charges. Average PPO adjustment: 30-45% of revenue (ADA 2024 Fees Survey). Typical dentist writes off <strong>$3-6M over a 30-35 year career</strong>.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-mint">FFS Migration</span>
      <h4>FFS practices grew 6% → 16%</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.9rem">Direct migration to cash/membership models. The market is moving where Clerri sits. <strong>30% of dentists dropped networks Q4 2024</strong> — those practices need somewhere to land.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-zest">Adoption</span>
      <h4>~40% of practices offer subscription plan</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.9rem">Practices with membership see 76% more visits, 146% more procedures, <strong>172% higher cash production</strong> vs. uninsured. Steep part of the S-curve.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Top 10 US DSOs heading into 2026 <span style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--muted);font-weight:400">— Becker's Dental</span></h2>
  <div style="overflow-x:auto">
    <table class="data-table">
      <thead><tr><th>#</th><th>DSO</th><th>Practices</th><th>Backer</th><th>Clerri Status</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>01</td><td><strong>Heartland Dental</strong></td><td>1,800+</td><td>KKR + Ontario Teachers'</td><td>Conquest (uses Coast Vantage One)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>02</td><td><strong>Aspen Dental</strong></td><td>1,300+</td><td>The Aspen Group</td><td><span class="pill pill-mint">Existing Clerri/Membersy</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td>03</td><td><strong>PDS Health</strong></td><td>~1,100</td><td>Pacific Dental Services</td><td>Conquest (no proprietary plan)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>04</td><td><strong>MB2 Dental</strong></td><td>800+</td><td>Charlesbank-adjacent</td><td>Within footprint</td></tr>
        <tr><td>05</td><td><strong>Smile Brands</strong></td><td>600+</td><td>—</td><td>Conquest (runs OneSmile)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>06</td><td><strong>Sonrava Health</strong></td><td>~600</td><td>—</td><td>Within footprint</td></tr>
        <tr><td>07</td><td><strong>Smile Doctors</strong></td><td>580+</td><td>—</td><td>Within footprint (ortho)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>08</td><td><strong>Affordable Care</strong></td><td>425+</td><td>—</td><td>Within footprint</td></tr>
        <tr><td>09</td><td><strong>Dental Care Alliance</strong></td><td>400+</td><td>—</td><td>Within footprint</td></tr>
        <tr><td>10</td><td><strong>Specialized Dental Partners</strong></td><td>250+</td><td>—</td><td>Within footprint</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <p style="color:var(--ink-soft);font-size:0.9rem;font-style:italic;max-width:65ch">Top 10 combined ≈ 7,800 practices. Clerri claims 7-of-10 — the conquest targets are <strong>Heartland and PDS Health</strong> (Aspen is already a customer; see ICP page for displacement strategy). The TAM expansion within existing 7 (driving enrollment velocity) is likely faster ROI than displacement of the remaining 2-3.</p>

  <h2>Messaging hooks <em>by stat.</em></h2>
  <div data-section="market">
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="market-01-ppo-hook" data-section="market" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">"30% of dentists dropped networks last year" — lead hook for paid + content</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="market-02-writeoff-hook" data-section="market" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">"$3-6M lifetime PPO write-off" — ROI calculator hook</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="market-03-72m-hook" data-section="market" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">"72M uninsured adults" — patient-side directory hook</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="market-04-ffs-hook" data-section="market" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">"FFS 6%→16%" — DSO executive deck talking point</div></div></label>
  </div>

  <div class="note-block">
    <div class="note-label">Market context notes <span class="note-saved">✓ saved</span></div>
    <textarea data-note="market-notes" placeholder="Updated stats to track, new ADA HPI surveys, competitive macro shifts..."></textarea>
  </div>

  <div class="topic-foot">
    <a href="/clerri/foundation"><span class="dir">← Prev</span><span class="name">01 · Foundation</span></a>
    <a href="/clerri/competitors"><span class="dir">Next →</span><span class="name">03 · Competitors</span></a>
  </div>

</div>
</ClerriLayout>
